topic.title: ZeroNet + Tor = 1 Tracker
topic.body: I got ZeroNet working with Tor. But that resulted in seeing only 1 oder even 0 Tracker. I stopped Tor and now I have 7 tracker. What can I do to raise the tracke while using Tor?

1630441420_15Ef8fbH5j5WZuMNoKum5u6WYFguX.body: Why is ZeroNet dying? Where is the developer? I wasn't here for a time. I just thought, ZeroNet was a good choice. What do we have for alternatives?

1631096303_1FfhKMAy1xwaRvaofCgaaMuRMa7M7.body:
> [xcape2net](#comment_969_1GJc2vm4vJjAKsFoFJ2D3gGmKiRac2kfnz): Are you using Synchronite?

I'm testing it right now and have many trackers now (73/103). What is Synchronite? Yes, a trackerlist. Is it legit?

> [swashbuckler](#comment_68_13UJZwpkQASN9unpc9hLhmwyauXzzatQgQ): Recently I often have Trackers: 0/63 and files sync can take up to few days...Zeronet Tor TrackersHow to fix 0 trackers? How and where to get more trackers?Almost no ZN trackers available

Thanks for these infos.

> [xcape2net](#comment_969_1GJc2vm4vJjAKsFoFJ2D3gGmKiRac2kfnz): Are you using Synchronite?

That works fine. Thx!
